> so talking about automation, how do you decide what to automate
  and what to test manually and how much test should be automated:

    - so basically, deciding what to automate depends on multiple factors
      like frequency of execution, stability, and business impact

    - to begin with, i usually prefer to automate repetitive and stable test cases
      ,especially regression scenarios, because they are executed frequently and
      save a lot of time.

    - from my experience, critical functionalities like login, navigation and core
      workflows are good candidates for automation

    - on the other hand, i prefer to keep dynamic or frequently changing features
      for manual testing, because automation maintenance becomes high

    - ideally, we focus on automating around 60-80% of stable and high-priority
      scenarios, especially regression and critical paths

    - the remaining scenarios can be tested manually based on need

    - so basically, the goal is to balance automation and manual testing
      to achieve maximum efficiency and coverage


